## Production Deployment (Firebase Serverless)

### 1. Configure default project
Open [`.firebaserc`](file:///Users/sema/Documents/code/work/gitme/.firebaserc) and change `your-firebase-project-id` to your actual Firebase project ID.

### 2. Configure Cloud Function Secrets
Before deploying, set your secrets and configuration variables in Firebase:
```bash
# Set your secure authentication token
npx firebase-tools functions:config:set tinyhub.token="your_real_secret_token"

# Set your signed token signature key for GET workaround
npx firebase-tools functions:config:set tinyhub.signing_secret="your_secure_signing_key"

# Set allowed CORS origins (comma-separated list)
npx firebase-tools functions:config:set tinyhub.origins="https://<your-project-id>.web.app,http://localhost:5000"
```

### 3. Deploy to production
```bash
npx firebase-tools login
npx firebase-tools deploy
```

